    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="910"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d910">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.008 North Pacific/208: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 19, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>307. Your 536, November 12, 8 p.m. The Counselor of the Japanese Embassy has made
                    to the Department an oral statement of the views of the Japanese Government in
                    regard to the Alaska fisheries situation. A memorandum of the conversation which
                    took place will be forwarded in an early mail.<note n="69" xml:id="d910fn69">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Department expects shortly to forward to the Embassy for presentation to the
                    Foreign Office a comprehensive memorandum on the salmon fishery situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
